text: Rezonville-Vionville is a commune in the Moselle department in Grand Est in north-eastern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Rezonville (the seat) and Vionville.Arrêté préfectoral 30 November 2018 ==See also== * Communes of the Moselle department ==References== Category:Communes of Moselle (department) Category:States and territories established in 2019 Category:Populated places established in 2019
title: Rezonville-Vionville
